videos.headline: Oklahoma uses 2 plays to score TD
videos.description: Following a long run, Rodney Anderson bounces off a few defenders for a 4-yard rushing touchdown.

videos.headline: Mayfield didn't start, but was hyped up anyway
videos.description: Baker Mayfield did not get the start against West Virginia, but was pumping up the crowd like usual.

videos.headline: Mayfield in for Oklahoma's second drive
videos.description: After not getting the start, Baker Mayfield is now the quarterback for Oklahoma starting the second drive.

videos.headline: Anderson shows off agility for 58-yard run
videos.description: Rodney Anderson makes some impressive cuts on his way for a 58-yard gain for the Sooners.

videos.headline: Mayfield throws TD after entering the game
videos.description: Baker Mayfield is hyped after connecting with CeeDee Lamb for an 8-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: West Virginia airs it out for 51-yard gain
videos.description: Chris Chugunov launches a pass downfield to David Sills V who escapes a defender and gains 51 yards.

videos.headline: Crawford coughs up the football on the 12-yard line
videos.description: West Virginia was putting together a great drive until Justin Crawford can't handle the toss and Oklahoma is there to recover.

videos.headline: Mayfield collecting mileage in the air with 56-yard toss
videos.description: Baker Mayfield sees Marquise Brown breaking away from his defender and hooks up with him for a gain of 56 yards.

videos.headline: Anderson cruises in for 2nd rushing TD
videos.description: Rodney Anderson streaks to the sideline and crosses the goal line for his second rushing touchdown of the first half.

videos.headline: McKoy bursts up the seam for 36 yards
videos.description: West Virginia runs the wildcat effectively gaining 36 on the ground with Kennedy McKoy.

videos.headline: Trickery from West Virginia leads to red zone opportunity
videos.description: Chris Chugonov is lined up as a wide receiver and is tossed the ball which left Marcus Simms wide open downfield for a 35-yard pitch-and-catch.

videos.headline: McKoy punches it in on 4th-and-goal
videos.description: West Virginia gambles on 4th-and-goal and comes away with points after Kennedy McKoy pushes through the line for the touchdown.

videos.headline: Suprise onside kick almost works out for West Virginia
videos.description: West Virginia surprises Oklahoma with an onside kick, but the ball was illegally touched a half yard short of 10 yards, so Oklahoma gets great field position.

videos.headline: Samia, Oklahoma get chippy with West Virginia
videos.description: Dru Samia has some words for West Virginia and then gets physical which results in an unsportsmanlike conduct penalty and an ejection.

videos.headline: Anderson has career high 3 rushing TDs
videos.description: Rodney Anderson scores his third rushing touchdown of the first half, this time from 17 yards out.

videos.headline: Mayfield racking up passing yards
videos.description: Baker Mayfield connects with CeeDee Lamb for a great catch-and-run getting the Sooners all the way down to the 1-yard line.

videos.headline: Anderson dives for 4th rushing TD
videos.description: Rodney Anderson soars into the end zone for his fourth rushing touchdown of the first half against West Virginia.

videos.headline: Mayfield slings 124th career TD
videos.description: Baker Mayfield moves into second place in Big 12 history with 124 career touchdown passes, this one to Mark Andrews for 14 yards.

videos.headline: Riley: 'That's great Big 12 football'
videos.description: Oklahoma head coach Lincoln Riley has his team up 45-10 at the break and is excited for the way Baker Mayfield is playing.

videos.headline: McKoy charges in for 2nd TD run
videos.description: Kennedy McKoy waits for the play to develop and charges for the 15-yard score.

videos.headline: Mayfield tosses 3rd TD
videos.description: Baker Mayfield and Grant Calcaterra work together for the 18-yard passing touchdown.

videos.headline: Oklahoma fans didn't want that West Virginia ball
videos.description: Following the extra point, Oklahoma fans take the ball that was kicked in to the stands and effectively got rid of it by throwing it out of the stadium.

videos.headline: Oklahoma backup QB throws 46-yard TD
videos.description: Kyler Murray replaces Baker Mayfield after getting the start earlier and throws a laser to Myles Tease who shakes off defenders and scoots in for the touchdown.

videos.headline: Mayfield: 'It's always chippy with them'
videos.description: Baker Mayfield said this game against West Virginia always has some fire, but he wanted to be the bigger man in this game and grow up from last week.

videos.headline: Oklahoma with a statement win
videos.description: Steve Levy and Brian Griese discuss why this impressive showing against West Virginia means more than just College Football Playoff discussions.

videos.headline: Oklahoma tops West Virginia on senior day
videos.description: Baker Mayfield misses the coin toss and the opening drive, serving his punishment after a crude gesture to Kansas bench last week, but he scores three touchdowns on 281 passing yards to lead the Sooners to a 59-31 win.

videos.headline: Oklahoma continues to put on a show
videos.description: Baker Mayfield and the Oklahoma Sooners case for the College Football Playoff is looking good after a blowout of West Virginia.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF (Oklahoma continues to put on a show) 2017/11/25 ODV ENHL

videos.headline: Mayfield caps emotional week with brilliance
videos.description: After a trying seven days in the spotlight, the Heisman frontrunner keeps calm and delivers an excellent senior day performance.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Mayfield caps emotional week with brilliance) 2017/11/25 ESHEET ENHL
